originalText.text: Th staff at this location are so rude and slow. They refuse to process returns and insist on you calling or emailing customer service. After they refused to take a return, customer service said they had no reason to not accept the return and apologized on behalf of the store. The team only wants to make commission not actually help do their job. Avoid this location.

originalText.text: Bought a pair of pants here during friends and family sale. Great selection. Free alterations. Above all incredible customer service. They listen and know their product. For fashionable and comfortable jeans this place can’t be beat. And you get a great reusable tote to take your purchase home in.

originalText.text:
Took my jeans for alternation, which I bought from an outlet store, the staffs welcomed us with smile and warm greeting. I mean, I can feel their passion about what they are doing and I can feel that they are trying to fulfill our need instead of trying over sell to get more money. We tried couple more jeans and made additional purchases with pleasure. We left those jeans for alternation. Seems the tailor failed to get to the store on time, but I do need those jeans before weekends. I am very glad after I reached to them and explained my situation, they were able to confirm our pants will be altered as a priority and finally I get my jeans on time.
The jeans are in great quality whereas the staffs are incomparable.
Will visit this store again if I want more jeans.

Seems all the AG Jeans got some great people! The SoHo store, Woodbury store. It’s really hard to complain. They got good quality jeans, good service, and the people. Amazing company.
